I was happy to get this hotel for $159/night - though internet was slow and added $16 dollars per day (though it included all calls - or so i thought until i got my bill and they had charged me $40 worth of long distance calls - they were promptly removed).	There are 3 and 4 star hotels just down the street from this one, and half the price.	It is much pricier than what you will find in the U.S. but if you like breakfast it may be worth it.	You are paying a premium price for being in the centre of the city and staying in a well maintained hotel, but I thought it was worth it.